results.name: Decimal expansion of Pi^4/96.
comment: Also the sum of the series Sum_{n>=0} (1/(2n+1)^4), whose value is obtained from zeta(4) given by L. Euler in 1735: Sum_{n>=0} (2n+1)^(-s) = (1-2^(-s))*zeta(s).
For the partial sums of this series see A120269/A128493. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Sep 02 2019
results.author: _Iaroslav V. Blagouchine_, Mar 11 2018
